    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="424"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2405</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Japanese Government accept and confirm the resolution adopted at the meeting
                    of the representatives of the bankers groups of the United States, Great
                    Britain, France and Japan at Paris on May 11 and 12, 1919, for the purpose of
                    organizing an international consortium for financial business in China:
                    Provided, however, that the acceptance and confirmation of the said resolution
                    shall not be held or construed to operate to the prejudice of the special rights
                    and interests possessed by Japan in South Manchuria and Eastern Inner
                    Mongolia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
